<item>
            <title>[LU-16848] Remove legacy gss pipefs and lgssd code</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16848</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The original GSS support in Lustre was implemented using a patched version of the equivalent NFS tool from nfs-utils, eventually being forked and copied into lustre source tree.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since, 2 new tools were added that replaced it: lsvcgssd and a linux keyring support with lgss_keyring.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(my understanding so far).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s sure is that lgssd is not more used for a while, code has been touched since 2008, and in the actual source tree, there is even not a way to build it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As Kerberos support is improved recently, let&apos;s get rid of this old code which is making harder to maintain GSS code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
